issues.title: Engine Oil Pump Drive Chain Failure
issues.description: The oil pump drive chain can stretch or fail, leading to complete loss of oil pressure and potential catastrophic engine damage. This is a known issue affecting the M838T engine.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement, oil pump chain replacement with updated parts
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid high RPM operation when engine is cold, monitor oil pressure closely

issues.title: Hydraulic Active Suspension Failure
issues.description: The ProActive Chassis Control (PCC) system can experience hydraulic pump failures, accumulator leaks, and sensor malfunctions, resulting in suspension that won't adjust or gets stuck in one mode.
symptoms: Vehicle stuck in one suspension mode
issues.fix_description: Replace hydraulic pump, accumulators, or suspension struts depending on failure point
issues.prevention: Regular hydraulic fluid checks, avoid aggressive driving over rough surfaces

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels can experience delamination, particularly around high-stress areas like door frames and rear spoiler mounts, causing visible separation of carbon fiber layers.
symptoms: Bubbling or raised areas on panels
issues.fix_description: Panel replacement or professional carbon fiber repair
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, proper storage, gentle washing techniques

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Rebooting
issues.description: The IRIS infotainment system frequently freezes, reboots spontaneously, or becomes unresponsive, affecting navigation, climate control, and vehicle settings.
issues.fix_description: Software updates or complete infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid using system during startup

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The electronic door handles can fail to operate properly, preventing entry or exit from the vehicle. The mechanism can stick or the electronic actuator can malfunction.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism and actuator
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of moving parts, gentle operation of handles

issues.title: Brake System Overheating
issues.description: Under track or aggressive driving conditions, the brake system can overheat, leading to brake fade, warped rotors, and potential brake failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake rotors and pads, upgrade to carbon ceramic brakes if available
issues.prevention: Allow cooling periods during track use, upgrade brake fluid regularly

issues.title: Engine Mount Degradation
issues.description: Engine mounts can deteriorate prematurely, causing excessive engine vibration and movement, particularly noticeable at idle and during acceleration.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine mounts with updated versions
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular inspection during service

issues.title: Electrical System Parasitic Drain
issues.description: Various electrical modules can cause parasitic battery drain when the vehicle is parked, leading to dead batteries and requiring frequent jump starts.
issues.fix_description: Diagnose and replace faulty control modules, update software
issues.prevention: Use battery tender for long-term storage, regular battery testing

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Actuator Problems
issues.description: The turbocharger wastegate actuators can fail, causing overboosting, underboosting, or erratic boost pressure, affecting engine performance and potentially causing damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace wastegate actuators and related vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance, use high-quality fuel, allow proper warm-up

issues.title: Airbag System Malfunction
issues.description: Various airbag sensors and control modules can malfunction, triggering warning lights and potentially disabling the airbag system during a collision.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty sensors, control modules, or wiring harnesses
issues.prevention: Avoid water damage, gentle cleaning of interior sensors

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock
issues.description: In hot weather conditions, the fuel system can experience vapor lock, causing fuel starvation, rough idle, and stalling issues.
issues.fix_description: Install updated fuel system components and heat shields
issues.prevention: Park in shade when possible, keep fuel tank more than half full

editorial.hero_blurb: The 570S strikes the perfect balance between McLaren's racing DNA and daily usability. With 562 horsepower and telepathic handling, it delivers genuine supercar thrills without the intimidation factor.
editorial.essence: The 570S represents McLaren's sweet spot - accessible enough for daily driving yet explosive enough to embarrass cars costing twice as much. It's the thinking enthusiast's supercar, offering pure driving joy without unnecessary complexity.
editorial.heritage: Launched as McLaren's entry-level Sports Series in 2015, the 570S marked the brand's return to more accessible supercars after the legendary F1 and MP4-12C. Built on McLaren's carbon fiber MonoCell II chassis, it carries forward the company's Formula 1 expertise into a more attainable package.
editorial.design_philosophy: McLaren's designers pursued function-first beauty, with every curve serving aerodynamic purpose. The 570S embodies minimalist aggression - clean lines, dramatic dihedral doors, and that unmistakable McLaren silhouette that prioritizes airflow management over flashy styling.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct race car derivative, the 570S spawned the track-focused 570S GT4 that competed successfully in various GT racing series worldwide, proving the platform's inherent capability and McLaren's racing pedigree.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.8L twin-turbo V8 is a masterpiece of linear power delivery, building thrust relentlessly from 3,000 rpm with minimal turbo lag. It feels naturally aspirated in its responsiveness while delivering crushing mid-range torque that defies physics.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed dual-clutch transmission shifts with surgical precision in Track mode or creams along smoothly in Comfort. Paddle response is instant, making heel-and-toe downshifts feel like telepathic communication with the drivetrain.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The adaptive suspension transforms character completely between modes - compliant enough for cross-country touring yet razor-sharp when unleashed. The carbon fiber tub provides incredible rigidity while the suspension geometry delivers neutral, confidence-inspiring balance.
editorial.steering_feel: Electro-hydraulic power steering offers genuine feedback and perfect weighting. Turn-in is immediate and precise, with the steering communicating exactly what the front tires are doing without being twitchy or nervous at speed.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon ceramic brakes provide race-car stopping power with incredible pedal feel. Initial bite is strong but progressive, allowing precise modulation while delivering fade-free performance on track with minimal effort required.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated growl that builds to an intoxicating wail at redline. The twin-turbo V8 produces a distinctive metallic edge overlaying deep bass notes, with pops and crackles on overrun that never feel artificial or overdone.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who want McLaren performance without the maintenance nightmares of earlier models. Perfect for enthusiasts seeking a true driver's car that can handle daily duties while delivering weekend track thrills.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers wanting maximum luxury appointments, extensive cargo space, or those intimidated by supercar attention. Also not ideal for those seeking the ultimate track weapon - the 600LT better serves that role.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 570S represents McLaren's most user-friendly supercar without compromising the core driving experience. Early examples offer tremendous value, but ensure maintenance records are complete as McLaren ownership still requires specialized care.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
